<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e104969.figure21>
    dc:description "Figure 21. Coenosia nigerrima, male. A Lateral view, B head, frontal view, C thorax, dorsal view, D abdomen, dorsal view, E fifth sternite, F cercus, dorsal view (SEM), G cercus and surstylus, dorsal view, H cercus, surstylus and phallic complex, lateral view, I phallic complex, lateral view, J phallic complex, detail of distal tip. Scale bar: 1 mm (A), 0.5 mm (B-D), 0.2 mm (E-H), 0.05 mm (I-J). Hypandrium, spicules on ventral surface - red arrows." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/882089" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e104969.figure22>
    dc:description "Figure 22. Coenosia nigerrima, female. A: Lateral view, B head, frontal view, C ovipositor, dorsal view, distal tip, D ovipositor, ventral view, distal tip, E spermathecae. Scale bar: 1 mm (A), 0.5 mm (B-D), 0.2 mm (E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/882090" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.81.e104969.figure23>
    dc:description "Figure 23. Geographical distribution of Coenosia nigerrima. A Subantarctic subregion records (Argentina, Chile), B Atlantic forest region records (Brazil). Biogeographic subantarctic subregion - green area, new records - black circle; bibliographic records - yellow triangle: bibliographic records in Brazil - black triangle." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/882091" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

